body:
Add an optional "layers" attribute which has the effect of enabling one or more layers for that module.  This is a pattern that is used for verification-only modules, e.g., a testharness, which want to enable a layer in a design-under-test, read from that, and then use that to drive ports on the module. The example below shows this:

```mlir
firrtl.circuit "Foo" {
  firrtl.layer @A bind {}
  firrtl.module private @Bar(
    in %a : !firrtl.uint<1>,
    out %b : !firrtl.probe<uint<1>, @A>
  ) {
    firrtl.layerblock @A {
      %0 = firrtl.ref.send %a : !firrtl.uint<1>
      %1 = firrtl.ref.cast %0 : (!firrtl.probe<uint<1>>) -> !firrtl.probe<uint<1>, @A>
      firrtl.ref.define %b, %1 : !firrtl.probe<uint<1>, @A>
    }
  }
  firrtl.module @Foo() attributes {layers = [@A]} {
    %bar_a, %bar_b = firrtl.instance bar @Bar(
      in a : !firrtl.uint<1>,
      out b : !firrtl.probe<uint<1>, @A>
    )
    %0 = firrtl.ref.resolve %bar_b : !firrtl.probe<uint<1>, @A>
    firrtl.strictconnect %bar_a, %0 : !firrtl.uint<1>
  }
}
```

With this PR applied, this compiles to the following Verilog (with a combinational cycle which we don't care about):

```verilog
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.61.0-162-g9e7dcc80c
module Bar_A(	
  input _a	
);

  wire _a_probe = _a;	
endmodule

module Bar(	
  input a	
);

endmodule

module Foo();	
  Bar bar (	
    .a (Foo.bar.bar_A._a_probe)	
  );
endmodule


// ----- 8< ----- FILE "groups_Foo_A.sv" ----- 8< -----

// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.61.0-162-g9e7dcc80c
`ifndef groups_Foo_A
`define groups_Foo_A	
bind Bar Bar_A bar_A (
  ._a (a)
);
`endif 
```

This needs to be added to the parser and the FIRRTL spec. Additionally, the ABI for this is not defined or correct, yet. Module `Foo` needs to _always have layer `A` enabled_ in order for it to be correct. I'm working on how to do this.

There are missing verifiers related to modules with enabled layers being instantiated under modules which don't have those same layers enabled. This should likely be an error, but it would be good if somebody thought through it deeply (@rwy7 😉).

Support in this PR is also added for FIRRTL parsing and emission. A similar example to the text above (adding annotations so modules are not optimized to nothing):

```
FIRRTL version 4.0.0
circuit Foo: %[[
  {"class": "firrtl.transforms.DontTouchAnnotation", "target": "~Foo|Bar>c"},
  {"class": "firrtl.transforms.DontTouchAnnotation", "target": "~Foo|Foo>d"}
]]
  layer Verification, bind:

    layer Foo, bind:
      layer Bar, bind:

  module Bar:
    input a: UInt<1>
    output b: Probe<UInt<1>, Verification>

    node c = UInt<1>(0)

    layerblock Verification:
      define b = probe(c)

  module Foo enablelayer Verification:

    inst bar of Bar

    node d = read(bar.b)
    connect bar.a, d
```
